content: I was completing the finger exercise due tomorrow (for L8) and am able to pass every test case except for one. If this is the case, should't calling the function with s1 = 'abcd' and s2 = 'cabaa' return True, since both strings have an 'a', a 'c', and a 'b'? subject: Finger Exercise Question

content: It's false because character d is only in one of the strings.
